íŸ@7a2e3dd71dd05016e054d2e073d96b3a1105d1608a53f7ff29cbf5bc63c7b76a⁄òTitle: title: polars profile
Path: Examples
Content:
Profile a lazy dataframe
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[a b]; [1 2] [1 4] [2 6] [2 4]]
    | polars into-lazy
    | polars group-by a
    | polars agg [
        (polars col b | polars min | polars as "b_min")
        (polars col b | polars max | polars as "b_max")
        (polars col b | polars sum | polars as "b_sum")
     ]
    | polars profile



```
íŸ@e2f8c5bbeb7741c1d94f299e171d3ff4d6399c4023b3531649914ec76499f9c2⁄Title: title: polars profile
Path: Notes
Content:
This will run the query and return a record containing the materialized DataFrame and a DataFrame that contains profiling information of each node that is executed.
The units of the timings are microseconds.
